---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Shad Khan and the themes behind this blog.">
  <section class="py-10">
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 sm:flex-row sm:items-start">
      <img
        src="/avatar.svg"
        alt="Shad Khan avatar"
        class="mx-auto size-32 rounded-full object-cover sm:mx-0"
        width="128"
        height="128"
      />
      <div class="prose-blog flex-1">
        <h1>About</h1>
        <p>
          I write about the practical side of software: AI-assisted development, backend systems,
          developer workflow, and the small decisions that make a codebase easier to live with.
        </p>
        <p>
          The point of this site is to keep the signal high. Posts should feel like notes from the
          bench: concrete, opinionated, and useful enough to come back to later.
        </p>
        <h2>Current Themes</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Working with coding agents without losing engineering taste.</li>
          <li>Designing feedback loops that catch regressions early.</li>
          <li>Keeping tools small, understandable, and pleasant to use.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
